message:
**And yes, I'm a noobie**I wrote JavaScript code that scrapes values from an HTML page. To develop and test, I copied the source from the target page and created my test pages from that. I then added JavaScript to those pages to get the functionality I wanted.
Now, I want to use Kynetx to take that JavaScript code and apply it to the live target page. How do I take JavaScript functions and put it into a Kynetx application? How do I then kickoff a JavaScript function to initiate the activity from within a Kynetx rule?
As an example, the much simplified HTML code below declares a JavaScript function and executes it.
<!doctype html public "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<body><h1>I got your HTML right here</h1>

<script text/javascript>

testfun = function (){
	alert ( "Yeehaw! JavaScript is working!" );
	};

testfun();	
</script>
</body></html>

I want to put "testfun" into a Kynetx app and execute it from a rule

rule first_rule {
select when pageview ".*" setting ()
 pre {

 }
 {
         emit <<
         testfun = function (){
         alert ( "Yeehaw! JavaScript is working!" );
         };
         testfun(); 
         >>
 }
}
